\c 35
\p
\v 1 And God said to Jacob, "Arise, go up to Bethel and live there and make an altar there to the God who appeared to you when you fled\f + \fr 35.1: \ft Qal, Inf. Con., + 2ms suffix, בָּרַח.\f* from Esau your brother."
\p
\v 2 And Jacob said to his household and to all who were with him, "Clear away\f + \fr 35.2: \ft Hiph., Impv., mp, סור.\f* the foreign gods which are in your midst and purify yourselves\f + \fr 35.2: \ft Hith., Impv., mp, טָהֵֽר.\f* and change\f + \fr 35.2: \ft Hiph., Impv., mp, חָלַף.\f* your cloak.
\v 3 And let us rise and go up to Bethel that I may make an altar there to the God who answers me on the day of my distress and has been with me on the way which I have gone."
\v 4 And they gave to Jacob all the foreign gods which were in their hand and the rings which were in their ears, and Jacob hid them\f + \fr 35.4: \ft Why did he hide them? Is he being sneaky, or is he putting them somewhere that no one will be able to reach and get their stuff back?\f* under the mighty tree that was near Shechem.\f + \fr 35.4: \ft What is the geographic significance of Shechem? And of this tree?\f* Rebekah died, and she was buried
